As the MoS revealed last week, five FIFA officials face criminal investgation in Switzerland arising from bid business and several are believed to be ExCo voters.

FIFA investigator Michael Garcia is separately investigating alleged breaches of FIFA’s ethics code by four ExCo voters from 2010: Angel Maria Villar Llona of Spain, Worawi Makudi from Thailand and Michel D’Hooghe from Belgium (all still on the ExCo) and Franz Beckenbauer of Germany.

As few as three invalidated votes for Qatar for 2022 would potentially be enough to have changed the outcome in the USA’s favour and one source believes voters contributing six or more Qatar votes are among those being probed.

