When the Mail on Sunday asked FIFA to clarify whether Russia and Qatar would keep the events regardless of the investigations, a spokeswoman said only: ‘The 2018 FIFA World Cup was awarded to Russia and the 2022 FIFA World Cup to Qatar. FIFA does not comment on speculation.’

A British inquiry into alleged fraud in the process is underway by the Serious Fraud Office and will be mentioned in a parliamentary debate on Monday arranged by campaigning MP Damian Collins.

